{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Function","title":"timeoutAddSecondsFull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"func","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeoutAddSecondsFull","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"priority","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"interval","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GSourceFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib21timeoutAddSecondsFull8priority8interval8function4data6notifyS2i_Sis5Int32VSvSgXCSgAJyAJXCSgtF"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/timeoutAddSecondsFull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeoutAddSecondsFull","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"priority","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"interval","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"function","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GSourceFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GDestroyNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The function is called repeatedly until it returns [const"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at which point the timeout is automatically destroyed and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the function will not be called again.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], this function operates at whole second"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"granularity. The initial starting point of the timer is determined by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"implementation and the implementation is expected to group multiple timers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"together so that they fire all at the same time. To allow this grouping,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"},{"type":"text","text":" to the first timer is rounded and can deviate up to one second"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from the specified interval. Subsequent timer iterations will generally run","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"at the specified interval.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given ","type":"text"},{"code":"interval","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources"},{"text":" for details","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of ","type":"text"},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want timing more precise than whole seconds, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] instead."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The grouping of timers to fire at the same time results in a more power","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and CPU efficient behavior so if your timer is in multiples of seconds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and you don’t require the first timer exactly one second from now, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use of [func"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_add_seconds","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] is preferred over"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This internally creates a main loop source using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_source_new_seconds","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attaches it to the main loop"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"context using [method"},{"code":"GLib.Source.attach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]. You can do these steps manually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if you need greater control.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is safe to call this function from any thread."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"time. See [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.get_monotonic_time","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a function to be called at regular intervals, with "},{"code":"priority","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timeoutaddsecondsfull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","role":"symbol","title":"Source","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSource","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" 